					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Eh, it's not a case of &quot;I'll vote based on something that isn't in the article&quot; I think, more like &quot;I wasn't sure if it was a reddish brown or a brownish red, but now that I've seen it together with green, I can better understand what it is.&quot;</p> <p>Regardless of the inspiration, even forgetting that there's no actual story here, this doesn't even use crosswords in any clever way. There is no mention of grid types or crossword variants, no clues, no cross-references. This is just the simplest dullest possible execution of the &quot;crossword puzzle format screw&quot; idea. I once said that format screws must be interesting beyond their format screw, and this one isn't</p> 
